---

Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @British Chicken Thighs{3}, @Peri Peri Seasoning{1%sachet}, @honey{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat.

Lay the chicken thighs flat onto a lined #baking tray{}. Once hot, roast on the middle shelf of your oven until browned and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{}, then pop it on top of the pan and allow to steam.

Meanwhile, drain the @Sweetcorn{160%g} in a sieve.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary.

> Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Once cooked, transfer the corn to a small #bowl{} and wipe the pan clean.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1} into small pieces.

In a medium bowl, combine the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%g} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing). Set aside.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the onion to the pan and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and cook for ~{1%minute}. Return the charred corn to the pan.

Pour in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the rice is cooked, add to the frying pan along with the @Butter{20%g}. Stir to combine, then remove from the heat.

Taste the rice and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything's ready, toss the @Wild Rocket{20%g} leaves in the dressing until evenly coated.

Share the chicken thighs between your #plates{}.

Serve the charred corn rice next to the chicken. Finish with a drizzle of @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{75%g} and the rocket leaves alongside. Enjoy!